# Codex full-repo review (2026-07-14, Critical #2): this file used to live
# at engine/.dockerignore, but docker-compose.yml's build context is the
# REPO ROOT (`context: .`), and Docker only honors a .dockerignore sitting
# at the context root — the one in engine/ was silently never applied.
# COPY engine/ ./ was therefore sweeping in engine/.env (real
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY etc. on a real deploy checkout), any local
# engine/node_modules, and test files, baking them into an image layer with
# no filtering at all. Patterns below are relative to this file's location
# (the context root), matching what engine/Dockerfile actually COPYs.
engine/node_modules
engine/.env
engine/test
engine/**/*.test.ts
web/node_modules
.git
.env
*.db
.jwt_secret
data/
.ccg/
